Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22summary_bullets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDear%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELast%20summer%2C%20I%20lost%20my%20job%2C%20and%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20significantly%20scaled%20back%20our%20spending.%20I'm%20back%20in%20the%20workforce%20now%20and%20making%20more%20than%20before%2C%20but%20both%20of%20us%20agree%20that%20since%20we%20can%20live%20on%20a%20lot%20less%2C%20we%20should%20do%20so%20and%20use%20the%20difference%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe're%20spending%20much%20less%20than%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20which%20is%20excellent.%20However%2C%20I%20think%20when%20you're%20no%20longer%20in%20emergency%20mode%2C%20it's%20wild%20not%20to%20spend%20the%20money%20if%20you%20have%20it.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20instance%2C%20our%20children%20all%20need%20new%20shoes.%20We're%20tall%20people%2C%20and%20their%20feet%20never%20seem%20to%20stop%20growing.%20Buying%20them%20all%20new%20shoes%20doesn't%20feel%20optional%20to%20me%2C%20but%20it%20does%20to%20my%20partner%2C%20who%20is%20still%20pretending%20we're%20surviving%20off%20only%20one%20income.%20They%20keep%20suggesting%20we%20put%20it%20off%20and%20see%20how%20long%20the%20kids%20can%20make%20their%20old%20shoes%20work.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhenever%20I%20say%20I'm%20planning%20to%20take%20the%20kids%20shoe%20shopping%20on%20a%20specific%20date%2C%20my%20partner%20either%20sabotages%20it%20by%20needing%20the%20car%20for%20something%20else%2C%20double%20booking%20us%20on%20%26quot%3Baccident%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20they%20outright%20throw%20a%20fit%20because%20this%20is%20an%20unnecessary%20expense.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20shoes%20are%20just%20one%20example%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20things.%20My%20partner%20has%20accused%20me%20of%20just%20wanting%20to%20return%20to%20old%20spending%20habits%2C%20and%20while%20it's%20not%20true%20%E2%80%94%20I%20am%20ready%20to%20exit%20emergency%20mode.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETired%20of%20Playing%20Poor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Playing%20Poor%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20get%20a%20new%20income%20stream%20or%20pay%20off%20a%20loan%2C%20we%20play%20a%20similar%20game%20as%20you%20and%20your%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Blet's%20pretend%20nothing%20changed%2C%20and%20treat%20our%20savings%20account%20like%20a%20standing%20bill%20of%20the%20same%20amount!%26quot%3B%20We%20agree%20to%20these%20things%20for%20the%20same%20reason%20you%20and%20your%20partner%20did%20%E2%80%94%20because%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20it%20even%20takes%2C%20but%20sometimes%20it%20doesn't.%20Either%20way%2C%20we're%20not%20beating%20ourselves%20up%20because%20we%20recognize%20that%20good%20ideas%20only%20go%20so%20far%20in%20real%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurviving%20month%20to%20month%20is%20very%20different%20than%20living%20well.%20When%20you're%20in%20survival%20mode%2C%20your%20goals%20are%20as%20simple%20as%20they%20are%20tragic%3A%20Don't%20lose%20the%20house.%20Don't%20lose%20the%20car.%20Try%20to%20keep%20the%20lights%20on.%20Try%20not%20to%20starve.%20When%20our%20goals%20are%20pared%20down%20to%20these%20basic%20essentials%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20important%20things%20tend%20to%20fall%20through%20the%20cracks.%20Things%20like%20eating%20healthier%20foods%20despite%20the%20mark%20up%2C%20helping%20our%20kids%20succeed%20socially%20by%20not%20clothing%20them%20in%20rags%2C%20and%20planning%20for%20the%20future%20by%20investing%20in%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Elife%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Surviving%20in%20the%20present%20trumps%20all%20these%20things%2C%20but%20saving%20a%20big%20pile%20of%20money%20just%20because%20you%20can%20certainly%20does%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20recognizing%20the%20difference%20between%20soft%20necessities%20like%20these%20and%20everyday%20indulgences%20can%20be%20difficult.%20Often%2C%20we%20have%20to%20experience%20the%20difference%20to%20see%20it.%20This%20is%20why%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20don't%20beat%20ourselves%20up%20over%20not%20permanently%20shifting%20a%20car%20payment%20to%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20because%20it%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20idea%20back%20when%20we%20paid%20off%20the%20loan.%20Unfortunately%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20your%20partner%20isn't%20as%20flexible%2C%20so%20the%20challenge%20is%20to%20help%20them%20see%20that%20living%20well%20is%20more%20important%20than%20living%20as%20cheaply%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20parenting%2C%20your%20partner's%20stubbornness%20on%20this%20point%20must%20feel%20extra%20frustrating.%20The%20idea%20that%20kids%20continue%20jamming%20their%20feet%20into%20too-small%20shoes%20until%20%E2%80%94%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20their%20toes%20pop%20through%20the%20top%3F%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20just%20absurd%2C%20it's%20irresponsible.%20Kids%20aren't%20great%20at%20advocating%20for%20themselves%2C%20which%20is%20why%20looking%20out%20for%20them%20is%20a%20parent's%20No.%201%20responsibility.%20Kids%20might%20casually%20mention%20their%20shoe%20is%20pinching%2C%20they%20may%20just%20whine%20that%20it's%20too%20tight%2C%20or%20they%20may%20suffer%20in%20silence%20because%20they're%20too%20busy%20having%20fun%20to%20notice%20silly%20things%20like%20footwear.%20But%20as%20adults%2C%20we%20know%20that%20painful%20blisters%20will%20be%20the%20least%20of%20their%20concerns.%20Wearing%20too-small%20shoes%20can%20lead%20to%20lifelong%20deformities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0When%20a%20parent%20doesn't%20recognize%20these%20things%2C%20they%20are%20either%20willfully%20negligent%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20from%20the%20tone%20of%20your%20letter%2C%20I%20doubt%20is%20the%20case%20for%20your%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20or%20they%20aren't%20experiencing%20the%20reality%20of%20parenting%20in%20a%20day-to-day%2C%20hands-on%20way.%20I%20suggest%20that%20you%20rectify%20this%20by%20showing%20them%20research%20on%20the%20dangers%20of%20too-small-shoes%2C%20and%20make%20them%20be%20the%20one%20to%20take%20the%20kids%20shopping.%20This%20way%2C%20they%20can%20see%20how%20hard%20it%20is%20to%20find%20good-condition%20shoes%20in%20thrift%20stores%20and%20say%20no%20to%20your%20kids'%20pleas%20for%20the%20latest%2C%20most%20expensive%20fashions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20shoes%2C%20however%2C%20look%20for%20opportunities%20to%20get%20your%20partner%20involved%20in%20the%20parts%20of%20your%20children's%20lives%20where%20they%20will%20see%20and%20hear%20your%20children's%20needs%20regularly.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20your%20kids%20are%20school-aged%20and%20car%20riders%2C%20you%20could%20have%20your%20partner%20take%20over%20the%20carpool%2C%20so%20they're%20the%20ones%20to%20hear%20your%20kids%20agonizing%20over%20blisters%20or%20despair%20over%20getting%20a%20tardy%20because%20their%20backpack%20zipper%20broke%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20hall.%20The%20parent%20who%20hears%20about%20these%20situations%20will%20always%20recognize%20their%20children's%20needs%20in%20a%20way%20the%20parent%20receiving%20the%20list%20of%20demands%20never%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20and%20your%20partner%20share%20the%20same%20goal%20of%20living%20on%20less%20so%20you%20can%20save%20more.%20The%20conflict%20is%20in%20the%20method.%20This%20shouldn't%20be%20too%20hard%20to%20solve.%20Sit%20down%20togeth