%20After%20Exit%20Polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20Kumari%20Selja%20told%20NDTV%20today%20she%20is%20confident%20her%20party%20will%20cross%2060%20seats%20in%20Haryana.%20An%20aggregate%20of%20seven%20exit%20polls%20have%20indicated%20the%20Congress%20will%20win%2055%20of%20Haryana's%2090%20seats%20-%20comfortably%20ahead%20of%20the%20halfway%20mark%20of%2046.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20warning%3A%20exit%20polls%20often%20get%20it%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20forecast%20of%20a%20Congress%20win%20in%20Haryana%2C%20the%20focus%20has%20moved%20to%20who%20would%20be%20the%20next%20Chief%20Minister.%20Former%20Chief%20Minister%20Bhupinder%20Singh%20Hooda%2C%20Randeep%20Surjewala%2C%20and%20Ms%20Selja%20herself%20have%20made%20their%20ambition%20known%20to%20the%20public%2C%20much%20before%20the%20election.%20This%20had%20raised%20a%20situation%20of%20infighting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Selja%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20she%20is%20very%20much%20in%20the%20race%20for%20the%20top%20post%2C%20but%20it%20won't%20be%20through%20the%20traditional%20%26quot%3Bstaking%20claim%26quot%3B%20optics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20state%20has%20groups.%20It%20is%20a%20part%20of%20politics.%20Why%20point%20fingers%20at%20Haryana%20or%20my%20party%3F%20This%20has%20been%20there%2C%20not%20just%20during%20elections.%20On%20the%20ground%20all%20of%20us%20have%20worked%20hard%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Selja%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20denied%20she%20would%20push%20her%20way%20through%20to%20stake%20claim%20for%20the%20top%20post.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20should%20I%20stake%20claim%3F%20Stay%20away%20from%20this%20mindset%2C%20that%20people%20stake%20claim.%20We%20have%20a%20level%20of%20seniority%2C%20who%20work%20hard%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20are%20committed%20to%20the%20party.%20Such%20people%20should%20be%20considered.%20Why%20should%20it%20be%20about%20staking%20claim...%26quot%3B%20the%20Congress%20MP%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Selja%20is%20not%20amenable%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20MLAs%20select%20the%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20as%20according%20to%20her%20this%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20factionalism.%20Instead%2C%20the%20high%20command%20should%20take%20the%20big%20decision%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20always%20felt%20in%20all%20these%20years%2C%20including%20during%20discussions%20with%20the%20high%20command%2C%20that%20a%20national%20party%20has%20to%20take%20a%20political%20view%20on%20things.%20And%20that%20is%20what%20should%20be%20the%20main%20consideration%20in%20choosing%20people%2C%20anytime%2C%20anywhere%2C%20any%20post%2C%20as%20to%20what%20we%20want%20to%20do%2C%20what%20we%20want%20to%20show%2C%20what%20we%20want%20to%20present.%20Apart%20from%20that%2C%20it%20is%20always%20the%20high%20command's%20last%20word%20which%20counts%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20even%20at%20that%20time%20and%20this%20time%2C%20counting%20MLAs%20etc%20is%20not%20a%20healthy%20thing%20for%20any%20party.%20I%20think%20it%20is%20the%20high%20command%20which%20should%20take%20a%20decision.%20Otherwise%20people%20get%20tied%20down...%20that%20I%20feel%20also%20leads%20to%20further%20factionalism%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Selja%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20asked%20people%20to%20come%20out%20from%20the%20mindset%20that%20sees%20voters%20as%20compartmentalised%20entities%20and%20not%20supportive%20of%20one%20another.%20Ms%20Selja%2C%20who%20is%20a%20Dalit%2C%20said%20people%20from%20all%20sections%20of%20society%20in%20Haryana%20support%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaryana%20can%20give%20me%20space.%20It%20is%20you%20people%20who%20have%20to%20come%20out%20of%20the%20mindset%20that%20Haryana%20is%20like%20this%2C%20Haryana%20is%20like%20that.%20I%20can%20assure%20you%20that%20I%20have%20support%20from%20all%20sections%20of%20society.%20Don't%20fall%20into%20this%20trap%2C%20propagated%20by%20vested%20interests.%20Move%20away%20and%20move%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20sections%20have%20supported%20the%20party.%20Dalits%20have%20supported.%20Not%20just%20them%2C%20others%20also.%20We%20have%20to%20move%20away%20from%20dominance%20of%20one%20segment%20because%20that's%20also%20not%20doing%20any%20justice%20to%20that%20one%20segment.%20You're%20isolating%20them%20and%20that%20doesn't%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Selja%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aggregate%20of%20exit%20polls%20shows%20the%20BJP%20could%20end%20up%20with%2027%20seats%20each%20in%20Haryana%20and%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20%C2%A0One%20exit%20poll%2C%20Jist-TIF%20Research%2C%20gave%20the%20BJP%20an%20outside%20margin%20of%2037%20seats%20-%20the%20maximum%20-%20in%20Haryana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECounting%20is%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728211200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F58r6hi08_kumari-selja_625x300_06_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fharyana-chief-minister-post-congress-leader-kumari-seljas-wont-stake-claim-strategy-to-seek-top-post-6728672%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Congress%20MP%20Kumari%20Selja%20told%20NDTV%20today%20she%20is%20confident%20her%20party%20will%20cross%2060%20seats%20in%20Haryana.%20An%20aggregate%20of%20seven%20exit%20polls%20have%20indicated%20the%20Congress%20will%20win%2055%20of%20Haryana's%2090%20seats%20-%20comfortably%20ahead%20of%20the%20halfway%20mark%20of%2045.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20demonizes%20immigrants.%20So%20why%20is%20he%20winning%20so%20many%20Latino%20votes%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20collection%20of%20Republican%20party%20imagery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc50397de5c8fd48345ece%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20community%20gathering%20center%20in%20Starr%20County%2C%20where%20support%20for%20Donald%20Trump%20nearly%20quadrupled%20in%202020.%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202015%2C%20when%20Donald%20Trump%20first%20descended%20from%20his%20golden%20escalator%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20Alexis%20Garc%C3%ADa%20was%20attending%20high%20school%20in%20the%20Texas%20border%20town%20of%20Rio%20Grande%20City.%20In%20those%20days%2C%20it%20seemed%2C%20everyone%20in%20his%20classes%20hated%20Trump.%20The%20town%20of%2015%2C000%20serves%20as%20the%20seat%20of%20rural%20Starr%20County%2C%20which%20is%2097%25%20Latino%20and%20has%20voted%20for%20the%20Democratic%20candidate%20in%20every%20presidential%20election%20for%20the%20past%20100%20years.%20Garc%C3%ADa%20was%20too%20young%20to%20vote%20in%202016%2C%20but%20he%20supported%20Bernie%20Sanders.%20That%20year%2C%20Hillary%20Clinton%20destroyed%20Trump%20in%20Starr%2C%20winning%2079%25%20of%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20Trump%20took%20office%2C%20Garc%C3%ADa%20began%20to%20find%20himself%20drawn%20to%20Trump's%20bombast.%20He%20liked%20the%20nicknames%20Trump%20came%20up%20with%20for%20his%20opponents%20%E2%80%94%20they%20reminded%20him%20of%20his%20own%20nickname%2C%20Pel%C3%B3n%2C%20meaning%20baldy%20for%20his%20buzzed%20hair.%20%26quot%3BTrump%20is%20like%20a%20schoolyard%20bully%2C%26quot%3B%20Garc%C3%ADa%20tells%20me%2C%20meaning%20it%20as%20a%20compliment.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202017%2C%20as%20a%20high-school%20senior%2C%20he'd%20become%20a%20full-fledged%20Trump%20supporter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20seeing%20how%20his%20classmates%20went%20after%20other%20Trump%20fans%2C%20Garc%C3%ADa%20chose%20to%20keep%20his%20political%20conversion%20to%20himself.%20%26quot%3BTienes%20nopal%20en%20la%20frente%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20friends%20would%20tell%20Trump%20supporters%20%E2%80%94%20you've%20got%20a%20cactus%20on%20your%20face.%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20insult%20was%20clear%3A%20You're%20only%20Mexican%20on%20the%20outside.%20When%20Garc%C3%ADa%20finally%20told%20people%20he%20liked%20Trump%2C%20he%20was%20denounced%20as%20a%20racist.%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20you%20do%20this%20to%20your%20own%20kind%3F%26quot%3B%20people%20would%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BComing%20out%20as%20a%20Republican%20was%20probably%20worse%20than%20coming%20out%20as%20an%20LGBT%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Garc%C3%ADa%2C%20who%20works%20at%20a%20local%20supermarket.%20%26quot%3BThey%20would%20shame%20you%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alexis%20Garc%C3%ADa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc4f087de5c8fd48345d30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexis%20Garc%C3%ADa%20was%20a%20Bernie%20Sanders%20supporter%20in%202016.%20Now%20he%20backs%20Donald%20Trump.%20%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Garc%C3%ADa%20felt%20like%20he%20was%20part%20of%20a%20minority%20in%20South%20Texas.%20MAGA%20was%20a%20sort%20of%20counterculture%20among%20Latinos%2C%20a%20tiny%20band%20of%20provocateurs%20who%20enjoyed%20pissing%20off%20the%20dominant%20Democrats.%20But%20beneath%20the%20surface%2C%20a%20seismic%20shift%20was%20underway.%20When%20the%20results%20were%20counted%20on%20election%20night%20in%20November%202020%2C%20Garc%C3%ADa%20was%20as%20shocked%20as%20everyone%20else%20to%20discover%20that%20Republican%20turnout%20in%20Starr%20County%20had%20nearly%20quadrupled%20from%202016.%20Joe%20Biden%20still%20won%2C%20but%20barely%20%E2%80%94%2052%25%20to%20Trump's%2047%25.%20Trump%20had%20gained%20more%20ground%20in%20Starr%20than%20in%20any%20other%20county%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20political%20analysts%20have%20been%20questioning%20whether%20Democrats%20are%20losing%20their%20long-standing%20advantage%20among%20Latino%20voters.%20How%20had%20a%20candidate%20who%20once%20called%20Mexicans%20%26quot%3Brapists%26quot%3B%20done%20so%20well%20in%20a%20Mexican%20American%20county%3F%20In%20July%2C%20before%20Biden%20exited%20the%20race%2C%20polls%20found%20his%20support%20among%20Latinos%20had%20fallen%20below%2050%25.%20And%20even%20since%20Kamala%20Harris%20won%20the%20nomination%2C%20polling%20has%20indicated%20she's%20likely%20to%20win%20no%20more%20than%2058%25%20of%20Latino%20voters%20%E2%80%94%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20what%20Democrats%20used%20to%20muster.%20That's%20especially%20significant%20this%20year%20because%20Trump%20doesn't%20need%20to%20win%20a%20majority%20of%20Latino%20support%20to%20retake%20the%20White%20House.%20If%20he%20can%20peel%20off%20enough%20of%20the%2036%20million%20Latino%20voters%2C%20especially%20in%20hotly%20contested%20swing%20states%20such%20as%20Arizona%20and%20Nevada%2C%20it%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20the%20margin%20of%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20empty%20street%20in%20Roma%2C%20Texas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc4f2b7de5c8fd48345d65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELike%20much%20of%20MAGA%20country%2C%20Starr%20County%20is%20rural%20and%20working%20class%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20has%20enabled%20Republicans%20to%20make%20inroads%20among%20Latino%20voters.%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20July%2C%20after%20Biden%20dropped%20out%20of%20the%20race%2C%20I%20traveled%20to%20Starr%20County%20to%20see%20why%20this%20longtime%20Democratic%20stronghold%20has%20been%20shifting%20steadily%20to%20the%20right.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20Starr%20differs%20from%20other%20border%20towns%20in%20some%20significant%20ways%2C%20especially%20in%20its%20relative%20dearth%20of%20recent%20migrants.%20But%20the%20county%20underscores%20how%20being%20Latino%20is%20becoming%20less%20predictive%20of%20how%20someone%20will%20vote.%20The%20area%20is%20working%20class%2C%20and%20its%20politics%20are%20similar%20to%20much%20of%20rural%20America.%20There's%20a%20reverence%20for%20law%20enforcement%20and%20the%20military%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20economic%20instability%2C%20and%20a%20nagging%20suspicion%20that%20liberal%20elites%20in%20Hollywood%20and%20on%20Wall%20Street%20think%20of%20locals%20as%20ignorant%20hicks.%20In%20Trump%2C%20they%20see%20a%20man%20who%20offers%20something%20different.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20tell%20me%20they're%20going%20to%20vote%20for%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Garc%C3%ADa%20says.%20%26quot%3BTrump%20is%20going%20to%20win.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20humid%20July%20morning%2C%20Benito%20Trevi%C3%B1o%2C%2077%2C%20is%20walking%20along%20the%20dirt%20road%20of%20his%20ranch%2C%20nestled%20among%20the%20thickets%20of%20Tamaulipan%20thornscrub%20that%20grow%20north%20of%20Rio%20Grande%20City.%20Reaching%20up%2C%20he%20grabs%20a%20bean%20pod%20from%20one%20of%20the%20large%20mesquite%20trees.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20grind%20these%20into%20flour%20with%20a%20hammer%20mill%20we%20built%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Trevi%C3%B1o%2C%20a%20biochemist%20and%20botanist%20by%20training%20who%20now%20runs%20a%20native-plant%20nursery.%20Like%20the%20mesquite%20and%20huisache%20that%20thrive%20in%20this%20arid%20climate%2C%20he%20has%20deep%20roots%20in%20Starr%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrevi%C3%B1o%20traces%20his%20family's%20ancestry%20back%20to%20the%20earliest%20Spanish%20colonists%2C%20who%20made%20their%20homes%20on%20thin%20ranches%20along%20the%20Rio%20Grande.%20When%20the%20US%20annexed%20half%20of%20Mexico%20in%201848%2C%20those%20Mexican%20ranchers%20suddenly%20became%20American.%20Instead%20of%20them%20moving%20to%20America%2C%20America%20moved%20to%20them.%20Today%2C%20many%20South%20Texans%20like%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20see%20themselves%20as%20more%20Tejano%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethan%20Mexican%20American.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%2C%20in%20part%2C%20why%20Biden's%20campaign%20struggled%20to%20get%20traction%20among%20many%20Starr%20residents.%20His%202020%20playbook%20for%20Latinos%20was%20built%20around%20celebrating%20immigrants%20and%20affording%20them%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20his%20slogans%20was%20%26quot%3BTodos%20con%20Biden%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EBut%20many%20here%20don't%20identify%20as%20immigrants.%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20was%20born%20in%201947%20and%20grew%20up%20helping%20his%20parents%20work%20the%20lands%20his%20family%20had%20been%20on%20for%20generations.%20He's%20American.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20almost%20everyone%20in%20his%20generation%2C%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20was%20raised%20as%20a%20Democrat%2C%20he%20says%2C%20for%20one%20simple%20reason%3A%20There%20were%20no%20Republicans%20in%20Starr%20County.%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20heard%20the%20word%20'Republican'%20growing%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20Republican%20Party%20here.%26quot%3B%20For%20more%20than%20a%20century%2C%20Democrats%20enjoyed%20complete%20control%20of%20local%20government%2C%20often%20running%20unopposed%20in%20general%20elections.%20That%20dominance%2C%20at%20its%20worst%2C%20led%20to%20graft%20and%20corruption%20as%20powerful%20families%20passed%20down%20elected%20offices%20like%20heirlooms.%20When%20Trevi%C3%B1o's%20father%20spoke%20out%20against%20the%20local%20leadership%20in%20Starr%2C%20the%20Democratic%20bosses%20found%20a%20way%20to%20show%20their%20displeasure%3A%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20claims%20that%20when%20officials%20decided%20to%20improve%20a%20dirt%20road%20that%20ran%20through%20the%20county%2C%20they%20left%20the%20stretch%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20home%20unpaved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Benito%20and%20Toni%20Trevi%C3%B1o%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc4f547de5c8fd48345d99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBenito%20and%20Toni%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20became%20Republicans%20after%20witnessing%20corruption%20in%20the%20local%20Democratic%20Party.%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20machine%20politics%20compelled%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20to%20turn%20away%20from%20the%20Democrats.%20He%20was%20also%20prodded%20by%20his%20wife%2C%20Toni%2C%20a%20chemist%20turned%20lawyer%20who%20moved%20to%20Starr%20from%20Houston.%20As%20an%20outsider%20and%20self-identified%20libertarian%2C%20she%20was%20shocked%20by%20the%20county's%20rampant%20cronyism.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20you%20a%20Democrat%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked%20her%20husband.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20a%20hard%20worker.%20You're%20very%20conservative%20in%20your%20values.%26quot%3B%20The%20Trevi%C3%B1os%20became%20Republicans%2C%20and%20today%20Toni%20serves%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Starr%20County%20GOP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20worst%20instances%20of%20machine%20politics%20were%20eradicated%20by%20the%201980s%2C%20many%20old-timers%20like%20Trevi%C3%B1o%20remain%20deeply%20suspicious%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Party.%20In%20South%20Texas%20counties%20where%20Democrats%20have%20controlled%20local%20politics%20for%20generations%2C%20Republicans%20can%20offer%20themselves%20as%20the%20party%20of%20something%20new.%20And%20polls%20indicate%20the%20same%20shift%20taking%20place%20across%20the%20country%3A%20Latinos%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20see%20Trump%2C%20rather%20than%20Harris%2C%20as%20the%20candidate%20offering%20a%20chance%20at%20major%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20any%20place%20embodies%20the%20dual%20identity%20among%20Latinos%20in%20Starr%20County%2C%20it's%20the%20Rancho%20Cafe%20in%20the%20tiny%20town%20of%20Roma.%20On%20the%20outside%2C%20the%20restaurant%20has%20the%20wooden%20facade%20of%20an%20Old%20Western%20saloon%2C%20complete%20with%20a%20covered%20wagon%20in%20the%20dirt%20parking%20lot.%20Inside%2C%20however%2C%20it's%20classic%20Tex-Mex.%20Traditional%20Mexican%20dresses%20hang%20for%20sale%20along%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20and%20the%20servers%20greet%20you%20in%20Spanish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rancho%20Cafe%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc4f747de5c8fd48345dba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Rancho%20Cafe%20%E2%80%94%20part%20Old%20West%20saloon%2C%20part%20Tex-Mex%20hangout%20%E2%80%94%20embodies%20the%20dual%20identity%20of%20local%20Latinos.%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20lunchtime%2C%20Aliriam%20Perez%20sits%20sipping%20a%20bowl%20of%20caldo.%20Both%20her%20parents%20are%20from%20Miguel%20de%20Alem%C3%A1n%2C%20a%20Mexican%20city%20across%20the%20border%20that%20would%20blend%20in%20seamlessly%20with%20Roma%20if%20it%20weren't%20for%20the%20heavily%20patrolled%20river%20separating%20them.%20Perez%20grew%20up%20mostly%20on%20the%20US%20side%2C%20though%20she%20crossed%20over%20frequently%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20family.%20Her%20mother%20was%20adamant%20that%20Perez%20never%20lose%20touch%20with%20her%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20she%20didn't%20want%20her%20daughter%20to%20become%20%26quot%3Bpocha%2C%26quot%3B%20Americanized.%20Though%20Perez%20at%20times%20rebelled%20against%20her%20mother's%20wishes%2C%20at%2034%20she's%20come%20to%20appreciate%20the%20importance%20of%20her%20Mexican%20heritage.%20Now%20that%20she%20has%20two%20boys%20of%20her%20own%2C%20she's%20raising%20them%20bilingual.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20part%20of%20their%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20where%20they%20come%20from.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20Perez%20wasn't%20very%20political.%20But%20that%20changed%20when%20she%20married%20a%20local%20police%20officer.%20In%202020%2C%20during%20the%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20protests%20that%20followed%20the%20murder%20of%20George%20Floyd%2C%20Perez%20was%20deeply%20offended%20by%20the%20way%20Democrats%20supported%20calls%20to%20%26quot%3Babolish%20the%20police.%26quot%3B%20It%20felt%20like%20an%20affront%20to%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20was%20%26quot%3Bout%20there%20putting%20himself%20in%20danger%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Breaking%20with%20her%20mother%2C%20who%20believes%20that%20it's%20crucial%20for%20Mexican%20Americans%20to%20vote%20against%20Trump%2C%20Perez%20began%20volunteering%20with%20the%20local%20Republican%20Party.%20As%20she%20sees%20it%2C%20a%20vote%20for%20%26quot%3Blaw%20and%20order%26quot%3B%20Trump%20is%20a%20way%20to%20both%20honor%20and%20protect%20her%20husband%20and%20other%20first%20responders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20maintain%20a%20significant%20advantage%20among%20Latinos%20like%20Perez's%20mother%2C%20first-generation%20immigrants%20who%20speak%20Spanish%20as%20their%20first%20language.%20But%20that%20advantage%20weakens%20among%20the%20second%20and%20third%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20not%20because%20American-born%20Latinos%20like%20Perez%20are%20more%20distant%20from%20their%20heritage%20but%20because%20they've%20started%20to%20prioritize%20other%20issues%20in%20the%20voting%20booth.%20The%20top%20two%20concerns%20among%20Latinos%20this%20year%20are%20the%20same%20as%20those%20for%20their%20fellow%20Americans%3A%20the%20economy%20and%20healthcare.%20In%20one%20recent%20poll%2C%20only%209%25%20of%20Latino%20voters%20cited%20immigration%20as%20their%20top%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarr's%20economy%20is%20propped%20up%20not%20only%20by%20law%20enforcement%2C%20including%20the%20Border%20Patrol%2C%20but%20also%20by%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry.%20During%20Garc%C3%ADa's%20childhood%2C%20he%20recalls%2C%20his%20immigrant%20father%20would%20make%20the%20long%20drive%20out%20to%20the%20Permian%20Basin%20in%20West%20Texas%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20as%20pipe%20fitter.%20Oil%20production%20has%20grown%20under%20Biden%2C%20and%20Harris%20says%20she%20has%20no%20plans%20to%20ban%20fracking.%20But%20to%20Garc%C3%ADa%2C%20it's%20obvious%20that%20Republicans%20are%20far%20more%20keen%20to%20expand%20drilling.%20Voting%20for%20Trump%2C%20as%20he%20sees%20it%2C%20is%20his%20best%20bet%20to%20keep%20his%20dad%20employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20%26quot%3Boil%20worker%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20a%20big%20part%20of%20Latino%20identity%20in%20swing%20states%20like%20Arizona%20and%20Nevada.%20Democrats%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20have%20long%20played%20to%20Latino%20voters%20by%20emphasizing%20the%20discrimination%20they%20face%20in%20the%20energy%20industry%20and%20law%20enforcement.%20But%20that%20appeal%20is%20beginning%20to%20lose%20its%20appeal.%20Perez%20says%20she%20knows%20racism%20exists%20in%20America%20%E2%80%94%20a%20white%20worker%20in%20an%20Alabama%20Dairy%20Queen%20once%20refused%20to%20serve%20her%20because%20she's%20Mexican.%20But%20she%20doesn't%20see%20discrimination%20as%20the%20province%20of%20any%20one%20political%20party.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20Democrats%20who%20are%20racist%20and%20there%20are%20Republicans%20who%20are%20racist%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Latinos%20still%20tell%20pollsters%20they%20consider%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20more%20welcoming%20to%20them%20than%20Republicans.%20But%20there%20are%20signs%20the%20political%20cohesion%20of%20%26quot%3BLatinidad%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20beginning%20to%20fracture.%20Across%20the%20country%2C%20Latino%20Republicans%20say%20they%20feel%20more%20able%20to%20wear%20their%20politics%20on%20their%20sleeve.%20When%20people%20give%20them%20a%20hard%20time%20about%20voting%20for%20Trump%2C%20they've%20adopted%20a%20proud%20and%20defiant%20comeback.%20%26quot%3B%C2%BFY%20qu%C3%A9%3F%26quot%3B%20they%20reply%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BSo%20what%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20home%20on%20his%20ranch%20along%20the%20northern%20edge%20of%20Starr%20County%2C%20Rick%20Guerra%20keeps%20one%20room%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20museum%20of%20his%20time%20in%20the%20Army%3A%20his%20vest%20from%20his%20days%20as%20a%20tank%20gunner%20during%20the%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%2C%20his%20boots%20from%20his%20deployment%20in%20Afghanistan.%20On%20one%20wall%2C%20there's%20a%20collection%20of%20medals%20and%20challenge%20coins.%20As%20a%20teenager%2C%20Guerra%20helped%20his%20father%20and%20brothers%20build%20this%20very%20house.%20After%20he%20retired%20from%20the%20Army%2C%20he%20moved%20in%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20two%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rick%20Guerra%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc4fed5ccfc192a55247e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERick%20Guerra%20wants%20America%20to%20return%20to%20the%20days%20of%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20when%20the%20military%20was%20a%20top%20priority.%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELeaning%20conservative%20since%20he%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20Guerra%20became%20a%20dedicated%20Republican%20during%20his%20time%20in%20the%20Army%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he'd%20like%20to%20see%20America%20return%20to%20the%20days%20of%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20when%20the%20military%20was%20flush%20with%20cash.%20Like%20many%20Latino-majority%20counties%20in%20Texas%2C%20Starr%20sends%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20its%20young%20men%20and%20women%20to%20the%20military%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%20Most%20families%20have%20at%20least%20one%20veteran%20in%20their%20family%20tree%2C%20and%20that%20has%20contributed%20to%20the%20fiercely%20pro-military%20tenor%20of%20the%20local%20political%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20another%20dynamic%20at%20play%20on%20Guerra's%20ranch%3A%20This%20is%20rural%20America%2C%20where%20Democrats%20have%20been%20hemorrhaging%20support%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%20Today%2C%20the%20political%20gulf%20between%20urban%20and%20rural%20areas%20is%20a%20greater%20divide%20than%20the%20split%20between%20North%20and%20South.%20While%20three-quarters%20of%20rural%20Americans%20are%20white%2C%20huge%20swaths%20of%20rural%20counties%20in%20Texas%20and%20other%20states%20are%20majority%20Latino.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20millions%20of%20Latinos%20are%20beginning%20to%20experience%20what%20demographers%20call%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2022%2F10%2F20%2Fmidterms-rural-urban-divide-resentment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erural%20resentment%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20like%20other%20MAGA%20supporters%2C%20they%20feel%20disrespected%20by%20politicians%20and%20the%20media%20on%20the%20urban%20coasts.%20And%20efforts%20by%20Democrats%20to%20counter%20such%20perceptions%2C%20like%20passing%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20to%20create%20energy%20jobs%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barrons.com%2Farticles%2Fbiden-rural-voters-big-spending-infrastructure-inflation-reduction-act-8df204b9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%20little%20effect%20on%20attitudes%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20Latinos%20and%20other%20rural%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20blue%20collar%2C%20you're%20blue%20collar%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20where%20you're%20from%2C%26quot%3B%20Guerra%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you're%20blue%20collar%2C%20you%20want%20a%20president%20who%20is%20going%20to%20get%20his%20hands%20dirty%20and%20do%20stuff%20for%20the%20country%20and%20its%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20working-class%20support%20in%20Starr%20has%20been%20most%20visible%20in%20the%20string%20of%20%26quot%3BTrump%20Trains%26quot%3B%20that%20have%20been%20taking%20place%20across%20South%20Texas.%20In%20June%2C%20at%20the%20first%20rally%20of%20the%20summer%2C%20I%20speak%20with%20a%20professional%20portrait%20photographer%20named%20Roel%20Reyes%20as%20he's%20adjusting%20the%20flags%20on%20his%20motorcycle%20on%20the%20southern%20edge%20of%20Route%2083.%20He's%20flying%20the%20Texas%20Lone%20Star%20flag%20next%20to%20the%20Stars%20and%20Stripes%3B%20on%20the%20front%20of%20his%20bike%20are%20two%20signs%20that%20proclaim%20%26quot%3BTRUMP%202024.%26quot%3B%20Reyes%20smiles%20as%20pickup%20trucks%20and%20other%20bikes%20pull%20over%20behind%20him%2C%20all%20of%20them%20flying%20Trump%20banners.%20Before%20long%2C%20the%20parade%20of%20vehicles%20snakes%2015%20miles%20southeast%20from%20Roma%20to%20Rio%20Grande%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20during%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Reyes%20helped%20organize%20the%20county's%20first%20Trump%20Train.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20riotous%20parades%20felt%20like%20a%20protest%20as%20much%20as%20a%20rally%2C%20a%20way%20to%20openly%20flout%20the%20COVID%20shutdowns%20being%20enforced%20by%20local%20Democrats.%20Reyes%20recalls%20getting%20plenty%20of%20%26quot%3Bsingle-finger%20salutes%26quot%3B%20from%20townspeople.%20But%20the%20trains%20also%20gave%20him%20the%20sense%20that%20Trump%20was%20more%20popular%20in%20Starr%20than%20the%20polls%20might%20indicate.%20During%20the%20rallies%2C%20he'd%20get%20waves%20from%20local%20folks%20he%20knew%20would%20never%20admit%20to%20supporting%20Trump%20in%20mixed%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20patrol%20vehicle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc50065ccfc192a552480f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Border%20Patrol%20is%20a%20major%20employer%20in%20Starr%2C%20creating%20a%20receptive%20audience%20for%20Trump's%20tough%20talk%20on%20immigration.%3Cp%3EJordan%20Vonderhaar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20puts%20the%20country%20first.%20He%20puts%20God%20first%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20for%20border%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Reyes%20says.%20Next%20to%20him%2C%20an%20off-duty%20Border%20Patrol%20agent%20who%20has%20joined%20the%20Trump%20Train%20nods%20in%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocal%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%20agree%20that%20the%20trains%20gave%20Trump%20an%20electoral%20advantage%20in%202020.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Democrats%20%E2%80%94%20following%20strict%20instructions%20from%20the%20Biden%20campaign%20to%20avoid%20spreading%20the%20virus%20%E2%80%94%20stopped%20knocking%20on%20doors%20and%20focused%20instead%20on%20their%20digital%20strategy.%20Republicans%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20kept%20staging%20the%20Trump%20Trains%2C%20knocking%20on%20doors%2C%20and%20throwing%20well-attended%20barbeques%20and%20%26quot%3Basadas.%26quot%3B%20Democrats%20have%20become%20accustomed%20to%20hemorrhaging%20support%20from%20working-class%20white%20voters.%20But%20now%20it's%20clear%20that%20more%20and%20more%20Latinos%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20overrepresented%20in%20the%20working%20class%2C%20especially%20in%20South%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20are%20flocking%20to%20the%20Republicans.%20Being%20Latino%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20no%20longer%20dictates%20how%20someone%20will%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20Train%20being%20held%20is%20small%2C%20but%20Reyes%20already%20has%20plans%20to%20hold%20larger%20rallies%20all%20across%20the%20border%20lands.%20This%20first%20train%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20like%20the%20trailer%20before%20the%20movie.%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20hard%20to%20hear%20him.%20Every%20few%20minutes%2C%20passing%20trucks%20honk%20their%20horns%2C%20their%20drivers%20waving%20out%20their%20windows%20at%20the%20sea%20of%20MAGA%20flags%20blanketing%20the%20dry%2C%20thorny%20landscape%20that%20once%20belonged%20to%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjack-herrera%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJack%20Herrera%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20who%20reports%20on%20how