%20software%20company%20Guidewire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHurricanes%20haven't%20significantly%20affected%20Florida%20home%20prices%2C%20real-estate%20data%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20this%20week%2C%20and%20the%20Sunshine%20State%20is%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-are-people-moving-florida-home-prices-cost-of-living-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20states%20to%20move%20to%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20real-estate%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eagents%20on%20the%20ground%20are%20still%20unsure%20what%20will%20happen%20next.%20Increasing%20chances%20of%20natural%20disasters%20and%20flooding%20coupled%20with%20high%20insurance%20bills%20and%20homes%20that%20remain%20relatively%20expensive%20can%20make%20homeownership%20in%20Florida%20a%20pricey%20%E2%80%94%20and%20risky%20%E2%80%94%20proposition.%20A%20few%20residents%20want%20out%2C%20local%20brokers%20said%2C%20while%20others%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20costs%20and%20plan%20to%20stay%20put.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22804c3e90-9d9e-442d-a9a2-deff25851676%5C%22%3EThe%20cost%20of%20insurance%20is%20making%20some%20home%20sellers%20lower%20their%20asking%20prices%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2027%2C%20the%20morning%20after%20Helene%20tore%20through%20the%20city%20of%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20real-estate%20agent%20Katie%20Mallah%20received%20a%20call%20from%20a%20client%20with%20a%20recently-listed%20three-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20home%20in%20the%20Shore%20Acres%20neighborhood%2C%20a%20collection%20of%20man-made%20islands.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20asked%20Mallah%20to%20slash%20the%20asking%20price%20of%20their%20house%2C%20which%20had%20sustained%20nearly%20three%20feet%20of%20water%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20wanted%20to%20get%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Mallah%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20said%2C%20'We'll%20demo%20everything%2C%20but%20we%20want%20to%20price%20it%20to%20just%20get%20out.%20So%20come%20up%20with%20that%20number.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pile%20of%20debris%20including%20a%20broken%20piano%20and%20dresser%20sits%20outside%20a%20damaged%20Florida%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fdbd975ccfc192a552c4cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20property%20in%20Shore%20Acres%2C%20Florida%2C%20impacted%20by%20Hurricane%20Helene.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Katie%20Mallah%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMallah%20chopped%20the%20listing%20price%20by%2040%25%2C%20lowering%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efrom%20%24375%2C000%20to%20%24225%2C000.%20Within%20hours%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20inundated%20with%20about%2025%20calls%20and%2050%20text%20messages%20from%20investors%20interested%20in%20tearing%20down%20the%20home%20and%20building%20a%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMallah%20set%20a%20Tuesday%20deadline%20for%20all%20offers%2C%20just%20five%20days%20after%20the%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20seller's%20rush%2C%20Mallah%20said%2C%20was%20the%20chilling%20effect%20rising%20insurance%20premiums%20are%20having%20on%20this%20segment%20of%20the%20market.%20Luxury%20buyers%20might%20be%20able%20to%20brush%20off%20the%20increased%20cost%2C%20she%20added%2C%20but%20for%20buyers%20of%20homes%20under%20%24500%2C000%2C%20it's%20becoming%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeal%20killer.%26quot%3B%20Mallah's%20client%20didn't%20want%20to%20sit%20around%20and%20wait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompass%20agent%20Heather%20Cameron%20is%20representing%20a%20%24474%2C900%20home%20for%20sale%20near%20a%20canal%20in%20Tampa%20that%20was%20also%20affected%20by%20the%20hurricane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20super%20expensive%20property%2C%20but%20the%20owner%20has%20spent%20%2460%2C000%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20on%20flood%20insurance%2C%20and%20that%20home%20got%20flooded%20during%20the%20storm%2C%26quot%3B%20Cameron%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20owners%20are%20still%20waiting%20to%20see%20how%20much%20their%20insurance%20will%20cover%2C%20but%20they%20are%20considering%20offering%20potential%20buyers%20a%20credit%20that%20would%20cover%20flood%20insurance%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20home%20has%20been%20on%20the%20market%20for%20a%20little%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Cameron%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20price%20point%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%94%20with%20what%20the%20flood%20insurance%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20makes%20it%20kind%20of%20an%20affordable%20house%20for%20most%20buyers%20in%20that%20price%20range.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221290%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Piles%20of%20debris%20outside%20suburban%20Florida%20homes%20after%20a%20hurricane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fdbdd05ccfc192a552c4de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221028%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20street%20in%20Shore%20Acres%2C%20Florida%2C%20where%20residents%20are%20attempting%20to%20rebuild%20after%20Hurricane%20Helene.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Katie%20Mallah%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFloridians%20face%20some%20challenges%20securing%20insurance.%20Major%20providers%20like%20Farmers%20Insurance%20and%20Bankers%20Insurance%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-condo-owners-prices-drop-insurance-hoa-taxes-increase-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epulled%20out%20of%20the%20state%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20under%20new%20FEMA%20guidelines%20premiums%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20state%20are%20expected%20to%20rise%20by%20over%20300%25%20in%20coming%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.miamiherald.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fenvironment%2Fclimate-change%2Farticle275058126.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Miami%20Herald.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202024%2C%20the%20average%20cost%20of%20flood%20insurance%20in%20Florida%20was%20%24781%20a%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nerdwallet.com%2Farticle%2Finsurance%2Fflood-insurance-florida%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20personal-finance%20company%20NerdWallet.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Many%20homewoners%20also%20buy%20home%20insurance%3A%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20typical%20Florida%20household%20paid%20over%20%2410%2C000%20for%20home%20insurance%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finsurify.com%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fflorida%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520average%2520home%2520insurance%2520cost%2520for%2520Florida%2Cinclude%2520Travelers%252C%2520Nationwide%252C%2520and%2520Security%2520First%2520Insurance.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20data%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20Insurify%2C%20and%20Capital%20Economics%20found%20those%20premiums%20are%20rising%20at%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-prices-drop-florida-texas-violent-weather-insurance-costs-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20fastest%20rate%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%2020%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalm%20Beach%20agent%20Holly%20Meyer%20Lucas%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emany%20homeowners%20who%20aren't%20required%20to%20purchase%20flood%20insurance%20choose%20to%20go%20without%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20homeowners%20have%20dropped%20flood%20insurance%20or%20whittled%20their%20own%20insurance%20down%20to%20the%20absolute%20minimum%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyer%20Lucas%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20creates%20a%20particularly%20thorny%20situation%20as%20flood%20and%20wind%20insurance%20are%20often%20separate%20policies%2C%20Meyer%20Lucas%20pointed%20out.%20So%2C%20if%20a%20homeowner%20lives%20outside%20traditional%20flood%20zones%2C%20they%20may%20forgo%20specific%20flood%20protection%2C%20but%20still%20pay%20for%20wind%20and%20homeowners%20insurance.%20But%20when%20they%20are%20hit%20with%20a%20historic%20storm%20surge%20like%20Helene%2C%20it%20becomes%20difficult%20to%20separate%20what%20was%20solely%20water%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20basically%20makes%20the%20home%20a%20total%20loss%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20flood%20insurance%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyer%20Lucas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeyer%20Lucas%20anticipates%20more%20situations%20where%20fed-up%20Florida%20homeowners%2C%20who%20may%20have%20more%20equity%20in%20their%20homes%20than%20cash%20to%20repair%2C%20choose%20to%20cut%20their%20losses%20and%20sell%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20needing%20to%20sell%20their%20homes%20because%20they%20can't%20afford%20the%20remediation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f2622ff-1172-4fa1-895b-3e6961ccf239%5C%22%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20predict%20if%20Helene%20will%20sink%20home%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20homebuyers%20still%20love%20Florida%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20risks%2C%20multiple%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it's%20hard%20to%20say%20whether%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereal-estate%20prices%20will%20immediately%20falter%20in%20the%20Sunshine%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20not%20seen%20an%20event%2C%20even%20one%20like%20Hurricane%20Ian%2C%20that%20has%20had%20an%20industry-shifting%20effect%20on%20the%20real-estate%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Jon%20Schneyer%2C%20the%20catastrophe%20response%20director%20at%20data%20firm%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECoreLogic%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20true%20that%20some%20people%20may%20leave.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Freal-estate%2Fst-petersburg-florida-homeowners-hurricane-insurance-cost-4bc92822%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20many%20homeowners%20in%20Shore%20Acres%2C%20Florida%2C%20a%20coastal%20town%20six%20miles%20outside%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20want%20to%20sell%20to%20escape%20the%20flooding.%20And%20some%20of%20the%20most%20dire%20forecasters%20predict%20that%20sell-offs%20like%20this%20could%20bring%20down%20property%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECameron%20told%20BI%20that%20Shore%20Acres%20was%20known%20for%20flooding%20before%20Helene%2C%20and%20while%20she%20can%20see%20more%20inland%20properties%2C%20which%20are%20not%20in%20flood%20zones%2C%20increase%20in%20price%2C%20many%20people%20prefer%20to%20rebuild%20or%20move%20locally%20rather%20than%20leave%20the%20state%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20people%20really%20want%20to%20live%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20the%20demand%20is%20still%20going%20to%20be%20very%20high%20to%20live%20here%20in%20Tampa%2C%20St.%20Pete%2C%20and%20Sarasota.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20some%20experts%20believe%20risks%20haven't%20been%20properly%20baked%20into%20home%20prices%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20%2450.2%20billion%20overvaluation%20in%20Florida's%20housing%20market%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D534a29e6991e74122e1032ab20dc489d4d6309a5eb455e3dba170ab18d8271ec%26postID%3D66fda877e5b540830042d828%26postSlug%3Dflorida-real-estate-worth-it-home-prices-insurance-hurricane-helene-2024-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41558-023-01594-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20Nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20and%20particularly%20coastal%20counties%2C%20but%20also%20in%20parts%20of%20Appalachia%20as%20well%20%E2%80%94%20housing%20markets%20are%20not%20efficiently%20pricing%20flood%20risk%20into%20home%20values%20and%20that's%20causing%20this%20housing%20bubble%20to%20occur%2C%