ne%20of%20those%20would-be%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20tech%2C%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20companies%20would%20opt%20to%20hire%20those%20who%20have%20done%20well%20more%20than%20complete%20classwork%2C%20according%20to%20Mona%20Mourshed%2C%20founding%20CEO%20of%20Generation%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20network%20focused%20on%20economic%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20number%20of%20openings%20for%20entry-level%20tech%20roles%20has%20been%20declining%20for%20about%20three%20years%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20multiple%20emerging%20markets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20experienced%20workers%20are%20sometimes%20willing%20to%20downshift%20to%20lesser%20roles%20if%20they've%20been%20laid%20off%2C%20Mourshed%20said.%20Some%20employers%20prefer%20it%20that%20way%2C%20she%20added%20%E2%80%94%20because%20they%20can%20get%20a%20bargain%20rate%20on%20someone%20who%20might%20have%20several%20years%20of%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeneration%20found%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.generation.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2FLaunchingATechRevolution_Generation_Jun2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2094%25%20of%20employers%20required%20that%20applicants%20for%20entry-level%20tech%20jobs%20have%20experience%20working%20in%20a%20related%20field.%20The%20sampling%2C%20completed%20in%20early%202023%2C%20involved%20employers%20in%20eight%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%2C%20hiring%20for%20technology%20positions%20across%20over%20a%20dozen%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20entry-level%20job%20has%20vanished%20in%20many%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Mourshed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22faa4fdab-34d9-4ef8-a2a6-84f5127b9eb1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EManagers%20don't%20want%20to%20babysit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20survey%2C%20Generation%20gathered%20data%20from%20some%201%2C300%20employers%20from%20November%202022%20to%20January%202023%20on%20what%20they%20required%20regarding%20work%20experience%20and%20formal%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMourshed%20noted%20that%20during%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20after%20%E2%80%94%20people%20in%20fields%20like%20tech%20often%20worked%20from%20home.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-jobs-middle-managers-return-to-office-burnout-pressure-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagers%20have%20reported%20feeling%20stressed%3C%2Fa%3E%20out.%20That's%20one%20reason%2C%20she%20said%2C%20why%20having%20workers%20who%20required%20less%20guidance%20was%20ideal%20for%20many%20bosses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20had%20very%20strong%20preferences%20to%20hire%20people%20who%20were%20more%20stand-alone%2C%20who%20they%20felt%20wouldn't%20require%20as%20much%20oversight%2C%20because%20everyone%20is%20working%20remotely%2C%26quot%3B%20Mourshed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20have%20also%20been%20holding%20onto%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-are-unbossing-workplaces-and-millennials-are-at-risk-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efewer%20middle%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20an%20insufficient%20middle%20layer%2C%20then%20what%20you%20begin%20to%20do%20is%20to%20increase%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%20entry-level%2C%26quot%3B%20Mourshed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20that%20even%20as%20the%20pandemic%20eased%20its%20grip%2C%20many%20employers%20didn't%20relax%20requirements%20for%20their%20starter%20tech%20hires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20never%20went%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Mourshed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20raising%20their%20standards%20for%20entry-level%20positions%2C%20some%20employers%20in%20various%20industries%20simply%20aren't%20posting%20as%20many%20of%20these%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20every%201%20million%20listings%20on%20Indeed%2C%20the%20share%20of%20entry-level%20roles%20fell%206.9%25%20between%20August%202022%20and%20August%202024%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%20In%20its%20analysis%2C%20Indeed%20categorized%20starter%20jobs%20as%20requiring%20no%20more%20than%20a%20year%20of%20experience%20or%20preferring%20no%20more%20than%20two%20years%20of%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Henninger%20is%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20Heller%20Search%2C%20a%20recruiting%20firm%20focused%20on%20executive%20tech%20leaders.%20In%20a%20prior%20role%2C%20he%20spent%20more%20than%2015%20years%20filling%20staff-level%20tech%20jobs.%20Henninger%20said%20that%2C%20for%20years%20now%2C%20many%20employers%20have%20been%20ratcheting%20up%20what%20they%20expect%20from%20those%20seeking%20starter%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-return-to-office-mandate-bosses-morale-productivity-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edangle%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20option%20have%20extra%20leverage%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20take%20a%20shot%20on%20a%20fresh%20college%20grad%20or%20someone%20that%20has%20one%20year%20of%20experience%20because%20someone%20has%20five%20years'%20experience%20and%20will%20be%20willing%20to%20take%20that%20same%20amount%20of%20pay%20because%20they%20can%20sit%20in%20their%20own%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Henninger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorey%20Moss-Pech%20is%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20Florida%20State%20University%20and%20author%20of%20the%20forthcoming%20book%20%26quot%3BMajor%20Trade-Offs%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20examines%20the%20relationship%20between%20students'%20majors%20and%20entry-level%20jobs.%20He%20told%20BI%20that%2C%20in%20many%20industries%2C%20frontline%20clerical%20jobs%2C%20which%20long%20served%20as%20springboards%20to%20higher%20positions%2C%20have%20been%20hollowed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoss-Pech%20also%20noted%20that%20with%20schools%20offering%20more%20degrees%20in%20areas%20like%20data%20science%2C%20there's%20greater%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20more%20people%20now%20have%20the%20kinds%20of%20skills%20that%20the%20tech%20companies%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Moss-Pech%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22030a368f-5b54-4837-818c-18f172a649ce%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20not%20all%20bad%20news%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Neef%2C%20director%20of%20the%20career%20center%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20hasn't%20seen%20a%20drop%20in%20interest%20from%20employers%20hoping%20to%20fill%20tech%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20a%20recent%20event%20on%20the%20school's%20flagship%20Urbana-Champaign%20campus%20for%20those%20seeking%20jobs%20in%20fields%20like%20science%2C%20tech%2C%20data%20analytics%2C%20and%20engineering%20drew%20more%20than%20300%20employers%20and%20some%208%2C700%20students%20over%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%201%2C500%20software%20engineering%20positions%20%E2%80%94%20full-time%20roles%20and%20internships%20%E2%80%94%20are%20posted%20on%20a%20job%20board%20the%20school%20runs%2C%20Neef%20said.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20the%20postings%20have%20five%20or%20fewer%20applicants%2C%20and%20about%2015%25%20have%20no%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeef%20said%20one%20reason%20some%20students%20might%20feel%20stymied%20in%20their%20search%20for%20a%20first%20job%20is%20that%20many%20tend%20to%20focus%20on%20companies%20with%20strong%20consumer%20brands.%20Yet%2C%20she%20added%2C%20there%20is%20an%20enormous%20opportunity%20with%20small%20to%20midsize%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20typical%20year%2C%20only%20about%20100%20employers%20would%20hire%20five%20or%20more%20graduating%20Illini%2C%20Neef%20said.%20Yet%2C%20some%202%2C500%20smaller%20employers%20tend%20to%20hire%20fewer%20than%20five%20of%20the%20university's%20grads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20always%20where%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20jobs%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20small%20and%20midsize%20employers.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20students%20aren't%20aware%20of%20them%20because%20the%20employers%20are%20regional%2C%20Neef%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudents%20may%20not%20perceive%20them%20to%20be%20as%20prestigious%2C%20but%20they%20have%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b93e299e-7bef-4f2c-a7ce-81377f30eeb3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHunting%20for%20experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20struggling%20with%20his%20job%20search%20after%20college%2C%20Rod%20Danan%20went%20on%20to%20become%20a%20career%20coach.%20Then%2C%20in%202021%2C%20he%20started%20a%20company%20called%20Prentus%20that%20uses%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20other%20tools%20designed%20to%20help%20job%20seekers%20land%20roles%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanan%20told%20BI%20that%20many%20of%20the%20students%20that%20he%20works%20with%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20internships%20because%20many%20employers%20appear%20to%20be%20trimming%20the%20programs%20that%20could%20help%20train%20the%20next%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENumbers%20from%20Handshake%2C%20a%20job%20site%20for%20college%20students%2C%20show%20employers%20pulled%20back%20last%20summer.%20The%20number%20of%20available%20internships%20created%20on%20Handshake%20dropped%207.5%25%20from%20May%202023%20to%20May%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20Tech%20internships%20fell%20by%2013.6%25%2C%20while%20professional%20services%20slots%20slid%20by%2015.8%25%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanan%20hears%20about%20a%20dearth%20of%20internships%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-picks-up-in-fall-low-openings-hurting-job-seekers-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20seekers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20need%20the%20experience%20before%20they%20graduate%2C