such%20technology%20has%20raised%20significant%20concerns%20about%20privacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormann%20Witzleb%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Chinese%20University%20of%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt's%20important%20to%20design%20guidelines%20for%20those%20systems%20that%20take%20proper%20recognition%20of%20the%20potential%20benefits%20that%20they%20have%2C%20but%20that%20also%20acknowledge%20they're%20not%20foolproof%2C%20and%20that%20they%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20interfere%20with%20(people's)%20rights%20in%20serious%20ways%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESteve%20Tsang%2C%20director%20of%20the%20SOAS%20China%20Institute%2C%20warned%20that%20the%20new%20cameras%20could%20be%20used%20for%20political%20repression%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20fighting%20crime.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20further%20step%20in%20making%20Hong%20Kong%20law%20enforcement%20closer%20to%20how%20it%20is%20done%20on%20the%20Chinese%20mainland%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Hoffman%2C%20a%20nonresident%20fellow%20at%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Asian%20Research%2C%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20difference%20is%20how%20the%20technology%20is%20being%20used.%E2%80%9D%20While%20Western%20democracies%20face%20their%20challenges%20with%20surveillance%20technology%2C%20she%20argues%20that%20the%20situation%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20is%20fundamentally%20different%20due%20to%20the%20legal%20framework%20supporting%20the%20government's%20authority.%20She%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20being%20monitored%2C%20that%20affects%20your%20behaviour%20and%20your%20feelings%20of%20freedom%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20CNN.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728195180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Flctp5q3o_hong-kong_625x300_25_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthis-city-is-expanding-its-cctv-network-despite-being-among-safest